Description: A very nice 90s Fender Foto Flame Telecaster Made in Japan, in a flamy tobacco sunburst. There are far less of the tobacco sunburst. You generally see the red with the yellow bursts for sale, and they sell for much more. This guitar is set up for a player who wants to maximize their potential, or even a collector who is starting out. This Telecaster has been upgraded to rail pick ups. Guitar has a nice glossy finish all the way around, as seen in the pictures. Guitar does have a couple scuffs as listed in the photos. No major damage or neck stress cracks around base. Guitar is also missing volume knob control. Other than that, the guitar plays awesome and for the price, you can’t beat it. Other than the pick ups, guitar is original, and has minimal fret wear. This guitar has very rich tone and a great sustain. The best way to describe this guitar when it’s not plugged in as just simply to call it a harp. Excellent harmonics! You will not be displeased with this guitar whatsoever. If you have any questions, please ask in advance so that I have a proper amount of time to respond. Guitar comes with a after market road runner hard shell case. These guitars are getting more scarce and this is a great player, and a great example of a Japanese version for the time period.
